 Introduction to the special issue on (related to space or existing in space) 
 analysis for farming-based money-flow experts 
 Gerald C. Nelson* 
 University of Illinois, Urbana-Champaign, 305 Mumford Hall, 1301 W Gregory Drive, Urbana, IL 61801, USA 
 
 Abstract 
 
 The goal of this special issue is to introduce farming-based money-flow experts to new (related to careful studying or deep thinking) approaches involving (related to space or existing in space) data. 
 This paper provides a brief history of the special issue and an introduction to von Thiinen' s model of the (things that decide other things) of land 
 use and rent that underlies all (related to space or existing in space) analysis. 
