 Keywords: (related to space or existing in space) analysis 
 
 The goal of this special issue is to introduce farming-based money-flow experts to new (related to careful studying or deep thinking) approaches involving (related to space or existing in space) data (data that include the co-ordinates on 
 the surface of the earth, sometimes referred to as georeferenced). The beginning/creation of this issue was two learning 
 workshops-at the International Association of Farming-based Money flow Meetings, Berlin, August 2000 
 and the American Farming-based Money flow Association Meetings, Chicago, August 2001. The format of 
 the workshops was a morning session with summary 
 papers and a series of afternoon hands-on sessions, 
 where people (who were part of a study, etc.) were able to experiment with software and data, working through a problem involving 
 (related to space or existing in space) data and ways of doing things. The four papers following this introduction (Nelson and Geoghegan, 2002; 
 Bell and Irwin, 2002; Little bull et al., 2002; Anselin, 
 2002) are based on the summary sessions. The remaining papers were selected from the submissions 
 in response to a call for papers to complement the 
 summaries. 
 
