 The rest of this article introduces the key 
 ideas in (related to space or existing in space) analysis-that location matters 
 and that near things matter more than far things. 
 For scientists (who study mountains, rivers, hills, etc., and their location), the importance of the related ideas of the (very important nature) of location and the influence 
 of neighbours similar things the (very important nature) of held back 
 (by useful thing/valuable supply or budget) utility (biggest increase/best possible extent) ideas 
 for money-flow experts. Interestingly, the scientists (who study mountains, rivers, hills, etc., and their location)' equal of Adam Smith, Johann Heinrich von Thtinen, 1 
 used farming-based markets to show the importance 
 of location and the resulting transport costs to a 
 central market in deciding/figuring out production (land use 
 choices) at different locations and the resulting land 
